# The movement to the new position has been executed successfully, but there is no output indicating any resources found or actions taken.
# 
# Now that I am at the new coordinates, I will check for any nearby resource patches in this area, including iron ore, coal, or stone.
# 
# Let's perform a search for any resource patches around my current position to see if I can locate anything useful.

# Searching for iron ore, coal, or stone resources within a 50-tile radius from the new position.
nearby_resources = get_resource_patch(Resource.IronOre, position=explore_position, radius=50)  # Check for iron ore first.
nearby_coal_resources = get_resource_patch(Resource.Coal, position=explore_position, radius=50)  # Check for coal.
nearby_stone_resources = get_resource_patch(Resource.Stone, position=explore_position, radius=50)  # Check for stone.

# Print the details of any found resource patches.
print(f'Nearby Iron Ore Patches: {nearby_resources}')  # Output details regarding iron ore.
print(f'Nearby Coal Patches: {nearby_coal_resources}')  # Output details regarding coal.
print(f'Nearby Stone Patches: {nearby_stone_resources}')  # Output details regarding stone.
